# ── API endpoints ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Deliberately NOT handled here. Public market-data/aggregate endpoints
# already set their own short Cache-Control (s-maxage 3-30s) directly in
# code -- see functions/api/*.js -- and precedence between a _headers rule
# and a Function-set header isn't something worth risking on a guess for
# routes that are already correct and already verified working. Every
# sensitive endpoint that lacked a Cache-Control header (billing, admin,
# auth, the referral redirect) got one added directly in its own Function
# code instead, for the same reason: certainty over a blanket rule here.
